{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"daa77d5d-e740-41e6-b144-9ba9b36c2922","content":"The `dump-collect` skill covers **collecting** dumps but not analyzing them. Here's how to analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Using `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file>.dmp\n```\n\nOnce inside, useful commands:\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of crashing thread |\n| `pe -lines` | Print last exception with source lines |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap overview (OOM diagnosis) |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` | Inspect other threads |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n\n### Quick triage sequence\n```\n> pe -lines          # check for an unhandled exception\n> threads            # find the faulting thread\n> setthread <id>\n> clrstack           # see what code was running\n```\n\n### Alternatives\n- **Visual Studio** (Windows) — open the `.dmp` directly, click \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n- **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS) — `dotnet-sos install`, then `lldb --core <dump>`\n- **WinDbg** (Windows) — load SOS via `.loadby sos coreclr`\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and walk through the analysis with you? If so, let me know the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d982db1d-5b9b-4a56-bc53-5b9abf78c727","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for \"Configure and collect crash dumps\" and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So that skill is not appropriate here.\n\nThere's no specific skill for analyzing dumps. Let me provide guidance on how to analyze the dump file using available tools like `dotnet-dump analyze`.\n\nLet me check what tools are available in the environment first, and then guide the user.","outputTokens":547,"requestId":"6402:36525B:646A61B:7008C5C:69EC1AF6"},"id":"aa26cee6-1ccc-4a94-bf22-582574702558","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:38:13.998Z","parentId":"f977276f-45d3-4e8d-97d9-cc40afe9d6b5"}
